snippet: Unlike previous demonstrations, dozens of people were reported arrested at a boisterous rally against the Kremlin on Sunday, including protest organizers.
abstract: Police and anti-government protesters clash outside the Kremlin walls, leaving 20 police officers injured, and dozens of protesters in jail; for Vladimir V Putin supporters, the violence seems to confirm suspicions that the anti-Putin protest movement that began in December is led by radical and would-be revolutionaries.

byline.original: By ELLEN BARRY and MICHAEL SCHWIRTZ
byline.contributor: Glenn Kates and Anna Tikhomirova contributed reporting.

lead_paragraph: Unlike previous demonstrations, dozens of people were reported arrested at a boisterous rally against the Kremlin on Sunday, including protest organizers.

headline.seo: At Moscow Rally, Arrests and Violence
headline.main: Arrests and Violence at Overflowing Rally in Moscow
